column1: From the same Proto-Germanic: Swedish trä ‎(“wood”), träd ‎(“tree”), Norwegian tre ‎(“tree”), Icelandic tré ‎(“tree”), English tree, Scots tree ‎(“wood, rod, stick”), North Frisian tre, trä ‎(“tree”), Middle Dutch tree ‎(“tree”), Gothic 𐍄𐍂𐌹𐌿 ‎(triu, “tree, wood, piece of wood”); From the same Proto-Indo-European: Albanian dru ‎(“tree, wood”), Welsh dâr ‎(“oaks”), Ancient Greek δόρυ ‎(dóru, “wood, spear”), Tocharian A or.
